Package: tmuxsaver
Version: 0.4.1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Koen Van der Kimpen <koen.vanderkimpen@smals.be>
Depends: tmux, bash (>= 4.0)
Recommends: systemd
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/kvanderkimpen/tmuxsaver
Description: Minimal tmux session saver focused on working directory and shell history
 Saves the working directory and bash/zsh history for each tmux session.
 No window or pane layout is preserved — just enough context to get back
 to where you were after a reboot.
 .
 Includes optional systemd user services for automatic save on logout
 and restore on login.
